You can run node.js applications from the command line.
You do this by first typing "node" then you type the node.js file you want to run.
if you use ubuntu, you need to use "nodejs" instead of "node".

To keep my application running on the server all the time i use something called PM2, which is a project manager.

by typing pm2 start appname it will run in the background on my server. to run an application in background
is called to deamonize application. 


